Compact Repo Definition

NTE (Narrative Tensor Engine)

A generative system that maps inputs onto archetypal narrative structures (Story Primes) to explore, compress, and construct meaning across domains.

RNE (Reliable Narrator Engine)

A validation system that enforces temporal consistency, causal integrity, identity alignment, and evidence bounds on generated narratives, ensuring outputs remain stable and truthful.

⸻

One-line difference

NTE tells the story.
RNE makes sure it’s not lying.

⸻

This separation is critical.

If they blur together, you either:
	•	hallucinate with confidence
or
	•	never say anything interesting

Keeping them distinct is what gives Pantheon both power and restraint.